# Scaffold Profiles Index (A–O)

## [STRICT] Purpose
- Provide a catalog of scaffold profiles derived from `PLANFORSCAFFOLD.md`.
- Allow selection of a profile and invocation of rule generation for a target repo.

## [STRICT] Triggers

### LIST_SCAFFOLDS
- Role: List available scaffold profiles and short descriptions

### SELECT_SCAFFOLD
- Role: Set active scaffold profile for subsequent generation
- Accepts: `id: A|B|C|...|O`

### GENERATE_FROM_PROFILE
- Role: Generate rules for the selected scaffold to `.cursor/rules/generated/`
- Accepts: `repoPath` (or `tree` pasted), `projectName?`
- Runs: `MAKE_RULES_FROM_SCAFFOLD` with profile-specific mapping

## [STRICT] Profiles
- A: Universal Baseline
- B: Frontend – SPA
- C: Frontend – SSR/Meta
- D: Backend – Node.js
- E: Backend – Python (FastAPI/Flask/Django)
- F: Backend – Java (Spring)
- G: Backend – .NET (ASP.NET Core)
- H: Full-stack Monorepo
- I: Serverless
- J: Mobile
- K: Data/ML
- L: Library/SDK
- M: CLI Tool
- N: IaC/Terraform
- O: Microservices Platform

